  Dao Browser Sparkle appcast template.

  This file is the canonical handwritten version. The real per-release
  appcast.xml that ships at $SUFeedURL is generated by Sparkle's
  `generate_appcast` tool (third_party/sparkle/bin/generate_appcast),
  which appends a new <item> for every signed artifact in the directory
  and signs each <enclosure> with the EdDSA private key from your
  login keychain.

  Maintenance:
    - Do NOT hand-edit appcast.xml in production. Always regenerate it
      via `generate_appcast dist/`.
    - This template lives in branding/ so it's version-controlled
      alongside the public key in src/patches/chrome/app/app-Info.plist.patch.
    - On a fresh clone, copy this template to dist/appcast.xml as a
      seed for the first signed release; `generate_appcast` will then
      take over.

  Channel: stable. Add a <sparkle:channel>beta</sparkle:channel> inside
  an <item> to publish a beta-only update; clients on the beta channel
  pick it up, stable clients ignore it.

  Minimum system version: matches LSMinimumSystemVersion in the app
  bundle Info.plist. Sparkle uses this to gate updates so users on
  older macOS don't end up with an app they can't launch.
-->
